					<description><![CDATA[<p>Want to stand out in a crowded marketing field? Read how six pros are getting found online now.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/get-found-online">6 Surprising Ways to Get Found Online in 2025</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com">WordStream</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Getting found online is no easy task in 2025. AI has both increased the competition for attention and reduced the opportunities to get it (hello, AI Overviews!).</p>
<p>That‚Äôs why it‚Äôs worth reviewing unexpected wins. What can we learn from that silly blog post or new marketing channel that struck a nerve or reached a new audience, generating 100x the traffic and awareness of anything else you‚Äôve created?</p>
<p>I asked six marketing pros to share a surprising strategy they used (or have seen others use) to get found online and offer an analysis of why it worked. With a little luck and creativity, we can all learn from their experience and replicate the magic.</p>
<h3>¬†Contents</h3>
<ol>
<li><a href="#let-your-fun-flag-fly-on-linkedin">Let your fun flag fly on LinkedIn</a></li>
<li><a href="#create-your-own-industry-awards">Create your own industry awards</a></li>
<li><a href="#agitate-a-fear-and-provide-a-real-solution">Agitate a fear and provide a real solution</a></li>
<li><a href="#turn-reddit-into-a-reliable-source-of-referral-traffic">Turn Reddit into a reliable source of referral traffic</a></li>
<li><a href="#post-podcast-snippets-on-youtube-shorts">Post podcast snippets on YouTube Shorts</a></li>
<li><a href="#use-tiktok-in-unexpected-ways">Use TikTok in unexpected ways</a></li>
</ol>
<div id="6-surprising-ways-the-pros-use-to-get-found-online"></div>
<h2>6 surprising ways the pros use to get found online</h2>
<p>These marketers found ways to beat the tsunami of content flooding our feeds and gave some tips so you can do the same.</p>
<div id="let-your-fun-flag-fly-on-linkedin"></div>
<h3>1. Let your fun flag fly on LinkedIn</h3>
<p><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/generating-leads-on-linkedin">LinkedIn</a> has always been the stuffy cousin of the social media family. The rule of thumb is to keep it professional there and hold the fun for other platforms. <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/verydemanda/">Amanda Nielsen</a>, B2B creator and founder of <a href="https://thotleaderlabs.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Thot Leader Labs</a> has found a surprising amount of success by doing, well, the opposite.</p>
<p>‚ÄúOne of my most viral LinkedIn posts used the smiley badge graphic people always post for promotions or major milestones,‚Äù she told me. ‚ÄúBut I paired it with the caption ‚Äòtried my best‚Äô and listed everyday wins like ‚Äòtook constructive criticism without crying‚Äô and &#8216;didn‚Äôt accidentally say love you bye at the end of the Zoom.‚Äô‚Äù</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/get-found-online-wordstream-amanda-1.webp" alt="Get found online - LinkedIn post from Amanda." width="428" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-92297 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/get-found-online-wordstream-amanda-1.webp 428w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/get-found-online-wordstream-amanda-1-214x300.webp 214w" sizes="(max-width: 428px) 100vw, 428px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/posts/verydemanda_happy-to-announce-i-feel-like-we-should-activity-7239299389364518913-HFgU?utm_source=share&amp;utm_medium=member_desktop&amp;rcm=ACoAAAfpBUkBZn1g_3AT-AQ7-zTMTBRIIDRYtto" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<p>Amanda said the post was meant to ‚Äúpoke fun at how overused that graphic had become and how people were using it for everything.‚Äù</p>
<p>It‚Äôs a little bit of a gamble to make fun of something so many people do, but the wager paid off. ‚ÄúThe post ended up with 9 million¬†impressions, 106K reactions, 3K comments, and 2.4K reposts,‚Äù Amanda said. ‚ÄúIt got way more traction than my typical audience, helped me grow my following significantly, and sparked conversations with tons of new people I wouldn‚Äôt have otherwise met. It even inspired me to turn it into a sticker on <a href="https://thotleaderlabs.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">thotleaderlabs.com</a>.‚Äù</p>
<p>Handclap emoji.</p>
<p>The tone in this example isn‚Äôt a one-off. Scrolling Amanda‚Äôs feed is like flipping through a stand-up comedian‚Äôs set notes‚Äîif the comedian only played to an audience of B2B professionals.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/get-found-online-wordstream-amanda-2.webp" alt="Get found online - LinkedIn post from Amanda." width="502" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-92298 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/get-found-online-wordstream-amanda-2.webp 502w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/get-found-online-wordstream-amanda-2-480x574.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 502px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/posts/verydemanda_yes-they-call-it-waiting-for-procurement-activity-7341868577169297409-h6Dq?utm_source=share&amp;utm_medium=member_desktop&amp;rcm=ACoAAAfpBUkBZn1g_3AT-AQ7-zTMTBRIIDRYtto" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<p>The lesson here is that getting found online is about standing out, not blending in. If everything around you is boring B2B content, a little sass in the SaaS will snap people out of scrolling‚Äîand make your brand a heck of a lot more memorable. As Amanda put it, ‚ÄúIt was a good reminder that sometimes the simplest ideas‚Äîespecially the ones that play with familiar formats‚Äîare what resonate most.‚Äù</p>
<p>Stepping out of our comfort zones can feel a little sketchy. Here are a few ways I‚Äôve seen marketers do it:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Create non-traditional content:</strong> Would anyone expect you to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/lead-generation-ideas">publish a comic strip</a> about cybersecurity? Probably not, so it‚Äôll definitely stand out.</li>
<li><strong>Have fun with your own foibles:</strong> We all have missteps in our professional lives. Share yours, especially the ones everyone experiences, and you‚Äôll be a lot more relatable and memorable.</li>
<li><strong>Mismatch the medium and the message:</strong> Most of us don‚Äôt want LinkedIn to become Facebook, but one of my most successful LinkedIn posts was a photo from my vacation. An occasional personal post can shake things up in the best way.</li>
</ul>
<div id="create-your-own-industry-awards">
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f4a1.png" alt="üí°" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /><strong>Ready for more ideas?</strong> Download <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/resources/increase-traffic-to-your-website?cid=Web_Any_BlogInContent_PPC_25WaysIncreaseTraffic_Download">25 Ways to Increase Traffic to Your Website</a></p>
</div>
<h3>2. Create your own industry awards</h3>
<ol start="2"></ol>
<p>Winning an industry award is a great way to get some attention for your brand. But what would happen if you created an entire awards program that recognized businesses in your field of excellence?</p>
<p><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/deesha-a-laxsav/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Deesha Laxsav</a>, senior brand marketing manager at <a href="https://clutch.co/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Clutch</a>, knows the answer to that question.</p>
<p>‚ÄúOne tactic that significantly increased engagement and traffic for Clutch was our Clutch Global Awards program,‚Äù she told me. The program led to ‚Äúa more than 100% week-over-week increase in <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/social-media-strategies/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">organic social engagement</a> and an over 55% increase in referral traffic.‚Äù</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/get-found-online-wordstream-clutch-post.webp" alt="Get found online - LinkedIn post from Clutch." width="492" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-92299 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/get-found-online-wordstream-clutch-post.webp 492w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/get-found-online-wordstream-clutch-post-480x585.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 492px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/posts/clutch-co_clutchglobal-activity-7331363244789424130-Eg7V?utm_source=share&amp;utm_medium=member_desktop&amp;rcm=ACoAAAfpBUkBZn1g_3AT-AQ7-zTMTBRIIDRYtto" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<p>Clutch is an online directory of B2B service providers from ‚Äúadvertising agencies in Amsterdam to mobile app developers in Mumbai.‚Äù The Clutch Global Awards program recognizes the highest-performing providers in various categories.</p>
<p>Deesha said the program&#8217;s success is bolstered by the ‚Äústrong focus on the promotional support we offered to the winners.‚Äù Specifically, Clutch provides award winners with a promotional toolkit featuring social media graphics, badges, <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/11/04/how-to-write-a-press-release">press release templates</a>, messaging, and more ‚Äúto help them easily share their recognition across their channels.‚Äù</p>
<p>Here‚Äôs where this strategy gets really cool. Much of the traffic and engagement comes from the award recipients linking back to their Clutch profiles. It‚Äôs like they‚Äôve created a whole bunch of partners drumming up <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/11/29/referral-traffic">referral traffic</a>.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/get-found-online-wordstream-applied-tech.webp" alt="Get found online - LinkedIn post from Applied Tech." width="485" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-92301 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/get-found-online-wordstream-applied-tech.webp 485w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/get-found-online-wordstream-applied-tech-480x594.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 485px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/posts/applied-tech_clutchglobal-msp-itservices-activity-7338588348258598915-m1_l?utm_source=share&amp;utm_medium=member_desktop&amp;rcm=ACoAAAfpBUkBZn1g_3AT-AQ7-zTMTBRIIDRYtto" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Source</a></em></p>
<p>Deesha said they‚Äôve invested in scaling that benefit. ‚ÄúFor the first time this year, we were able to <a href="https://clutch.co/agencies/digital-marketing#clutch-global-winners" target="_blank" rel="noopener">announce winners directly</a> within their respective categories on our directories,‚Äù she explained. ‚ÄúThis gave providers even more incentive to share their recognition and link to a specific, relevant page, enhancing both our visibility and SEO performance.‚Äù</p>
<p>‚ÄúWe‚Äôre always thinking about how to evolve and strengthen this campaign to not only recognize top-performing providers but also to drive greater awareness, engagement, and authority for the Clutch brand,‚Äù Deesha added.</p>
<p>It wouldn‚Äôt be too difficult to replicate aspects of Clutch&#8217;s awards program for any business. Here are a few ideas:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Create a landing page:</strong> Use it to highlight customers who use your product creatively.</li>
<li><strong>Host an awards event on social media:</strong> create several categories, and share the winners daily for a week. In any case, do as Clutch does and make it easy for winners to celebrate their awards publicly, linking back to your website in the process.</li>
<li><strong>Design a rating system:</strong> Sort of like Michelin stars for restaurants, give your customers a rating for things like sustainability, creative use, etc.</li>
</ul>
<div id="agitate-a-fear-and-provide-a-real-solution"></div>
<h3>3. Agitate a fear and provide a real solution</h3>
<p>When you publish a lot of content and one particular asset bests everything else you create for almost every important metric, you take a beat to figure out why it worked so well. That‚Äôs exactly what <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/einav-mor-4810613/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Einav Mor</a>, freelance copywriter and content creator, said happened when she published a guide titled ‚ÄúYou don&#8217;t know what you don‚Äôt know‚ÄîThe true cost of data inaccuracies‚Äù while still with her former employer.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/get-found-online-wordstream-appsflyer-guide.webp" alt="Get found online -Appsflyer guide." width="660" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-92302 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/get-found-online-wordstream-appsflyer-guide.webp 660w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/get-found-online-wordstream-appsflyer-guide-480x436.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 660px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.appsflyer.com/resources/guides/data-inaccuracies-true-cost/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<p>‚ÄúThis was a pretty extensive guide I&#8217;ve prepared back at AppsFlyer,‚Äù Einave explained. It was ‚Äúone of the most successful guides we‚Äôve put out. It outperformed anything else we published during that quarter for unique views, time on page, and <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/08/03/organic-traffic">organic traffic</a>.‚Äù</p>
<p>The guide was underpinned by a common fear among marketers: How can you drive growth when you can‚Äôt trust your data? But Einav said that was just one piece of the puzzle. ‚ÄúThe goal was to create a sense of FOMO that was backed up by hard numbers and practical steps to avoid costly data discrepancies.‚Äù</p>
<p>The result was a guide that made the problem feel real by highlighting the cold, hard costs of inaccurate marketing data. And Appsflyer promoted those facts to drive people to the content.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/get-found-online-wordstream-appsflyer-fb.webp" alt="Get found online -Appsflyer Facebook post." width="937" height="536" class="aligncenter wp-image-92303 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/get-found-online-wordstream-appsflyer-fb.webp 937w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/get-found-online-wordstream-appsflyer-fb-480x275.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 937px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.facebook.com/AppsFlyer/videos/the-true-cost-of-data-inaccuracies/433394551927600/?_rdr" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<p>‚ÄúIt effectively touched a nerve for any marketer out there and clearly explained the implications of relying on dodgy data for predictions and measurement,‚Äù Einav said. ‚ÄúBut it wasn&#8217;t just about sowing fear, which would&#8217;ve been a cheap trick. It was about giving tools for marketers to deal with daily uncertainty. And I believe our readers appreciated that.‚Äù</p>
<p>While the success of the guide may have been a little surprising, the formula isn‚Äôt hard to replicate:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Find a fear that your customers face: </strong>Take a survey and ask what vexes them most.</li>
<li><strong>Make it real with facts and data:</strong> Calculate the results of the survey or figure out the cost of the problem.</li>
<li><strong>Ease the tension with accessible solutions:</strong> <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/how-to-write-an-ebook">Publish a guide</a> that solves the problem with your product at its center.</li>
</ul>
<div id="turn-reddit-into-a-reliable-source-of-referral-traffic"><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f6d1.png" alt="üõë" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /><strong>Traffic and attention are just the beginning.</strong> Learn <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/resources/free-leads?cid=Web_WS_InContent_Guide_howtogetfreeleads_Download&amp;itm_source=wordstream&amp;itm_medium=blog&amp;itm_campaign=incontent_links">14 Ways to Get Free Leads (+Examples You Can Copy)</a></div>
<h3>4. Turn Reddit into a reliable source of referral traffic</h3>
<p>Sometimes, the surprisingly successful way to get found online isn‚Äôt a single ad or asset; it‚Äôs an entire marketing channel. That was the case for<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/megan-janan-j-54232b215/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> Megan Janan</a>, a marketing associate at<a href="https://www.whalesync.com/"> Whalesync</a>, who told me that Reddit is their top referral source, driving lots of traffic to their website.</p>
<p>Now, marketing on Reddit isn‚Äôt new; we‚Äôve researched and <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/reddit-marketing">written about it</a> several times. But it is notoriously hard to get a foothold on the platform. Redditors are quick to call out any overt marketing tactics. So when Megan told me about their success, I wanted to know how they achieved it.</p>
<p>‚ÄúReddit works because it‚Äôs quite BOFU [bottom of the funnel],‚Äù Megan said.‚ÄùUsers are either searching for a solution or are frustrated and venting. That‚Äôs when you can come in with your comment and solve their problem.‚Äù</p>
<p>Here‚Äôs an example Megan shared. A Redditor asked about entering custom formulas in a Notion document‚Äîa challenge that Whalesync can solve.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/get-found-online-wordstream-reddit.webp" alt="Get found online -Reddit discussion.," width="762" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-92304 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/get-found-online-wordstream-reddit.webp 762w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/get-found-online-wordstream-reddit-480x378.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 762px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/Notion/comments/uyt693/comment/mihrt4i/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Source</a></em></p>
<p>The reply came from a Whalesync employee. It added more context to other Redditors‚Äô suggestions and then provided a link to a post that dug in further.</p>
<p>It‚Äôs a tough balance, but when done correctly, the benefits will compound. ‚ÄúReddit works due to just the sheer amount of views you can get on a comment or thread, especially if you post in the right sub,‚Äù Megan said. ‚ÄúBut I personally view Reddit as quite ‚Äòevergreen,‚Äô so even though these posts are quite old, if people are searching for something similar, chances are they‚Äôll stumble on this Reddit thread and see our comment, and this can lead to referral traffic.‚Äù</p>
<p>Megan said they look for questions that directly relate to their product, like connecting two apps together. But they also have to get creative and find tangential challenges that their product may be able to solve. In the example above, for instance, the user just wanted to add custom formulas in Notion, and connecting to Sheets was a possible solution. In any case, Megan said the goal is to find ways to ‚Äúunblock users.‚Äù</p>
<p>How can you make Whalesync‚Äôs Reddit success your own?</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Find relevant subreddits:</strong> Start broad and narrow to niche topics. If you‚Äôre marketing a physical therapy practice, find healthcare subreddits, but also look for specific running or exercise threads.</li>
<li><strong>Link to your content organically: </strong>Look for opportunities to link out to your educational content, but make sure it tightly aligns with the question being asked. And if you don‚Äôt yet have a post that answers the question, there‚Äôs your next content idea!</li>
<li><strong>Think creatively when answering:</strong> If you have a popular product, Redditors are probably already discussing it, so you can simply join in. If your product isn‚Äôt a hot topic yet, you‚Äôll need to help people see how your product solves problems in ways they hadn‚Äôt considered.</li>
</ul>
<div id="post-podcast-snippets-on-youtube-shorts"></div>
<h3>5. Post podcast snippets on YouTube Shorts</h3>
<ol start="5"></ol>
<p>Some of the most popular <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/how-to-make-youtube-shorts/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">YouTube Shorts</a> ever feature speed cleaning a house, a transforming ‚ÄúCinderella‚Äù dress, and a tutorial to make your very own squishy ladybug toy. It‚Äôs not the first platform most marketers head to when they need to boost the performance of their B2B podcast.</p>
<p>To be fair, <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/sneh-ratna-choudhary/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Sneh Choudhary</a>, Chief Repurposer at <a href="http://scalingradcontent.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Scaling Rad Content</a>, was a little skeptical of it, too. ‚ÄúI help repurpose the podcast <a href="https://www.thefrictionlessexperience.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The Frictionless Experience</a>,‚Äù Sneh said. ‚ÄúIt was barely getting any views on YouTube, which is understandable because YouTube may not be the right platform for a B2B podcast. Isn‚Äôt LinkedIn a better platform for this?‚Äù</p>
<p>But then they ran an experiment, chopping up full-length podcast episodes and running them as Shorts. ‚ÄúAnd well, this worked better than I expected,‚Äù Sneh said.</p>
<p>The Shorts racked up over 30K views and lifted full-episode views by 48%. ‚ÄúAnd the best part,‚Äù Sneh said, ‚Äúwas the full-length episodes that weren‚Äôt getting enough views started getting noticed.‚Äù</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/get-found-online-wordstream-shorts.webp" alt="Get found online - YouTube channel." width="937" height="572" class="aligncenter wp-image-92305 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/get-found-online-wordstream-shorts.webp 937w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/get-found-online-wordstream-shorts-480x293.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 937px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.youtube.com/@TheFrictionlessExperience/shorts" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<p>To run the experiment, the team commissioned their video editors to create three or four clips. ‚ÄúBut that wasn&#8217;t going to be enough of a sample size to test our hypothesis,‚Äù Sneh said. ‚ÄúWill more short-form content shipped consistently help with the podcast&#8217;s visibility?‚Äù Sneh used OpusClip‚Äîan AI video clipping and editing tool‚Äîto scale that production, and so far, it‚Äôs working like a charm.</p>
<p>‚ÄúIt‚Äôs still early days, but this is exciting. I&#8217;m now running a second experiment where we chop up the podcast into 10 to 15-minute clips, the ideal length for YouTube videos. We&#8217;ll see how that goes.‚Äù</p>
<p>The lesson here is not to overlook marketing channels, even if they don‚Äôt seem to be the right fit at first. You don&#8217;t want to waste too much time on non-performing channels, though. Here are a few ideas to make the process more efficient:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Use <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/content-repurposing">repurposed content</a>:</strong> Don&#8217;t start from scratch. If you have blog posts, video yourself explaining the same content and try it on YouTube Shorts, TikTok, etc.</li>
<li><strong>Run intentional tests:</strong> Set specific goals for things like traffic or leads, and set a timeline to assess the results.</li>
<li><strong>Use AI:</strong> <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/best-ai-tools">AI tools</a> are great for things like summarizing content or quickly editing video.</li>
</ul>
<div id="use-tiktok-in-unexpected-ways"></div>
<h3>6. Use TikTok in unexpected ways</h3>
<p>Small family-owned businesses can sometimes struggle to get found online. They usually don‚Äôt have deep pockets or a team of marketing pros planning out <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/01/24/editorial-calendar">months&#8217; worth of social content</a>.</p>
<p>But <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/reginaldpowell/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Reggie Powell</a>, a <a href="https://theresultsphase.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">freelance tech and HR writer</a>, has unearthed a superpower these mom-and-pop shops have that‚Äôs hard for big businesses to replicate.</p>
<p>‚ÄúConsidering all the noise and unedited AI slop on the internet, the authenticity a local business can deliver is the new driver of the conversation on social media,‚Äù Reggie said.</p>
<p>By way of example, he pointed to Amici‚Äôs Pizza, a local restaurant in Mesa, Arizona. ‚ÄúA small business like Amici‚Äôs Pizza can‚Äôt compete on budget,‚Äù he noted. ‚ÄúWhat they did, which was really smart, was to use their TikTok account to pull back the curtain on what it‚Äôs like to run a small business.&#8221;</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/get-found-online-wordstream-amicis-tiktok.webp" alt="Get found online - Amici's TikTok" width="937" height="594" class="aligncenter wp-image-92306 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/get-found-online-wordstream-amicis-tiktok.webp 937w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/get-found-online-wordstream-amicis-tiktok-480x304.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 937px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.tiktok.com/@amici.pizza" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<p>In the videos, ‚ÄúWe get to meet the crew, see the good and bad of a long day making pies, and get to know what it takes to run a mom-and-pop pizza restaurant,‚Äù Reggie said. ‚ÄúThat‚Äôs how a small pizza shop in Mesa, Arizona, got over 300K followers.‚Äù</p>
<p>Amici‚Äôs TikTok triumphs are astounding. The most popular video has over 10 million views. People travel from thousands of miles and line up out the door for a buffalo chicken pizza or a plate of rigatoni. Even the local press is sharing the shop&#8217;s social success.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/get-found-online-wordstream-amicis-press.webp" alt="Get found online - News report on Amicis" width="937" height="643" class="aligncenter wp-image-92307 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/get-found-online-wordstream-amicis-press.webp 937w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/get-found-online-wordstream-amicis-press-480x329.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 937px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.azfamily.com/2024/12/02/mesa-pizza-shop-becomes-national-sensation-after-videos-go-viral-tiktok/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<p>Reggie said the strategy, if you can call simply showing up as yourself a strategy, has real staying power. ‚ÄúThey&#8217;ve become so successful because people feel like they know them,‚Äù he explained. ‚ÄúThey can identify with their struggles, and they can see what it actually takes to run a small business. This kind of real-life presentation will beat viral trends every time because authenticity doesn&#8217;t go away after a week.‚Äù</p>
<p>If you run a small business, you can leverage the power of personal connection to grow a following on social media in the same way. For example:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Share a day in the life:</strong> Capture the challenges, wins, and even the mundane parts of running your business.</li>
<li><strong>Share the inside jokes</strong>: Every industry has funny phrases and recurring themes specific to it. Create some videos highlighting them.</li>
<li><strong>Share your greatest creations:</strong> Whether it&#8217;s a mega-pepporoni pizza, a perfectly poured concrete patio, or a dazzling smile you helped create, let people see your best work and the process it took to get there.</li>
</ul>
<h2>How do you get found online in 2025? Be weird</h2>
<p>Great marketing has always been about getting attention. Some marketers will attempt to do that with pure scale, using AI to flood the feeds of potential customers.</p>
<p>But the examples we‚Äôve seen here go a different direction. They‚Äôre publishing unexpected content in new places. They‚Äôre breaking patterns, stopping scrollers, and building sticky brands that people remember and want to return to.</p>
<p>In 2025 and beyond, it‚Äôll be a lot harder to get found online by being the same, so try to be a bit weird and see what happens.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/get-found-online">6 Surprising Ways to Get Found Online in 2025</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com">WordStream</a>.</p>
